what does excess dietary protein cause? It is well established that excess dietary protein consumption leads to the formation of toxic metabolites that damage the liver. However, the scientific community is still arguing about whether the amount of dietary protein that is considered to be safe is actually safe or not. A study published in the journal Nature in May 2017 found that a high-protein diet leads to an increase in the production of a toxic metabolite called TMAO (trimethylamine N-oxide) which is produced in the liver
